@reminisce These are actually great catches!

1. I think you are right. What I could think about is to use a integer (32/64 bits) to represent the format. Each bit means sparse or dense. In this case, we can support up to 32/64 dimension tensors, which may be enough?

2/3. I am not sure about this. I raised an issue in there project so we can discuss directly with the authors. (https://github.com/tensor-compiler/taco/issues/108)

@moskewcz if you could try using my module, I would be interested in another feedback.

Thanks,
Al
